The paper focuses on compressing neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper proposes a new compression algorithm that utilizes an information theoretic bound and sparse regularization. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these sub-categories are most closely related to the topic of neural network compression. Additionally, the paper may also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as these sub-categories are also relevant to the topic of machine learning and neural networks.
